^-How To Survive An Enemy Preempt

|fp|2|at|A Marty Bergen Audio Visual Lesson  
^-|fp||cs||cp||ht|h|AT|^k@2    By Marty Bergen BBO nickname mbsez; |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.martybergen.com^*N|CP||ht|i|AT|^b@2
Every two months Marty Bergen and Howard produce an animated voice lesson. Using any computer with a browser (PC, Mac, iPad, etc.) you can hear Marty speak for several hours and thoroughly cover his topic. Not only does he discuss the basics, but he includes many "secrets of the experts" as well. I have found these movies very useful and enjoyable. 

If you are interested in seeing a demonstration lesson, click here |CP|1|AT|^*Htiny.cc/dngcdx^*N|CP||AT|. Note that the web site includes some free examples with some interesting bridge puzzles that Marty has created.

I have permission from Marty and Howard to use one example from each lesson to produce a bridge movie. This sampler will give you the flavor of the material that Marty presents and demonstrate his excellent teaching style.

In this movie I chose example hand ##5. In this sampler Marty presents his excellent teaching style particularly for those who wish to excel in Competitive Bidding. He also has "Make The Most Of Your Entries", "How To Play 3NT", "Drawing Trump - All, Some, or None", and "To Finesse or Not To Finesse" which all are superb for improving the declaring skill.  

Hand 5, my pick for this movie, is a 2@D overcall by your RHO. I wish I could present all 42 boards which deal with bidding over 2@D, 2@H, 2@S, 3@D, 3@S, 4@C, 4@H, and finally 4@S overcalls. I hop I can rise to the occasion. |ht|y|at|

